title: Astral Traveller
description: Time and a Word became the group's first release to enter the UK chart with a peak of No. 45.[2] It failed to chart in the US and received some mixed reviews from critics. During their UK tour in April 1970, guitarist Peter Banks was fired from the group. By the time of the album's release, he was replaced by Steve Howe who is photographed with the group on the North American issue. In 2003, the album was remastered with several previously unreleased tracks
